id Tkachenko]] (from November)\n|-\n| [[FC Torpedo-ZIL Moscow]]\n| [[Yevhen Kucherevskyi]] {{flagicon|UKR}}\n|-\n| [[FC Fakel Voronezh]]\n| [[Valeri Nenenko]] (until May)<br />[[Aleksandr Averyanov (footballer, born 1948)|Aleksandr Averyanov]] (from May)\n|-\n| [[FC Chernomorets Novorossiysk]]\n| [[Anatoly Baidachny]] (until April)<br />[[Viktor Zernov]] (April to June)<br />[[Sergey Andreyev]] (June to September)<br />[[Khazret Dyshekov]] (caretaker) (from September)\n|-\n|}\n\n==Standings==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n|show_limit=5\n\n|team1=SPA|name_SPA=[[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]]\n|team2=LOK|name_LOK=[[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]]\n|team3=ZEN|name_ZEN=[[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit St. Petersburg]]\n|team4=TOR|name_TOR=[[FC Torpedo Moscow|Torpedo Moscow]]\n|team5=KRY|name_KRY=[[FC Krylia Sovetov Samara|Krylia Sovetov Samara]]\n|team6=SAT|name_SAT=[[FC Saturn Moscow Oblast (1946-2011)|Saturn]]\n|team7=CSK|name_CSK=[[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]]\n|team8=SOK|name_SOK=[[FC Sokol Saratov|Sokol Saratov]]\n|team9=DYN|name_DYN=[[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]]\n|team10=ROT|name_ROT=[[FC Rotor Volgograd|Rotor Volgograd]]\n|team11=ROS|name_ROS=[[FC Rostov|Rostselmash]]\n|team12=ALA|name_ALA=[[FC Alania Vladikavkaz|Alania Vladikavkaz]]\n|team13=ANZ|name_ANZ=[[FC Anzhi Makhachkala|Anzhi Makhachkala]]\n|team14=TZM|name_TZM=[[FC Torpedo-ZIL Moscow|Torpedo-ZIL Moscow]]\n|team15=FAK|name_FAK=[[FC Fakel Voronezh|Fakel Voronezh]]\n|team16=CHE|name_CHE=[[FC Chernomorets Novorossiysk|Chernomorets Novorossiysk]]\n|win_SPA=17|draw_SPA=9|loss_SPA=4|gf_SPA=56|ga_SPA=30|status_SPA=C\n|win_LOK=16|draw_LOK=8|loss_LOK=6|gf_LOK=53|ga_LOK=24\n|win_ZEN=16|draw_ZEN=8|loss_ZEN=6|gf_ZEN=52|ga_ZEN=35\n|win_TOR=15|draw_TOR=7|loss_TOR=8|gf_TOR=53|ga_TOR=42\n|win_KRY=14|draw_KRY=7|loss_KRY=9|gf_KRY=38|ga_KRY=23\n|win_SAT=13|draw_SAT=8|loss_SAT=9|gf_SAT=45|ga_SAT=22\n|win_CSK=12|draw_CSK=11|loss_CSK=7|gf_CSK=39|ga_CSK=30\n|win_SOK=12|draw_SOK=5|loss_SOK=13|gf_SOK=31|ga_SOK=42\n|win_DYN=10|draw_DYN=8|loss_DYN=12|gf_DYN=43|ga_DYN=51\n|win_ROT=8|draw_ROT=8|loss_ROT=14|gf_ROT=38|ga_ROT=42\n|win_ROS=8|draw_ROS=8|loss_ROS=14|gf_ROS=29|ga_ROS=43\n|win_ALA=8|draw_ALA=8|loss_ALA=14|gf_ALA=31|ga_ALA=47\n|win_ANZ=7|draw_ANZ=11|loss_ANZ=12|gf_ANZ=28|ga_ANZ=34\n|win_TZM=7|draw_TZM=10|loss_TZM=13|gf_TZM=22|ga_TZM=35\n|win_FAK=8|draw_FAK=4|loss_FAK=18|gf_FAK=30|ga_FAK=53|status_FAK=R\n|win_CHE=5|draw_CHE=8|loss_CHE=17|gf_CHE=19|ga_CHE=54|status_CHE=R\n\n|col_CLGS=#90EE90|text_CLGS=[[2002\u201303 UEFA Champions League#Group stage|2002\u201303 UEFA Champions League Group stage]]\n|result1=CLGS\n|col_CL3=#D0F0C0|text_CL3=[[2002\u201303 UEFA Champions League#Third qualifying round|2002\u201303 UEFA Champions League Third qualifying round]]\n|result2=CL3\n|col_UCQR=#87CEFA|text_UCQR=[[2002\u201303 UEFA Cup#Qualifying round|2002\u201303 UEFA Cup Qualifying round]]\n|result3=UCQR\n|col_R=#FF8072|text_R=Relegation to [[2002 Russian First Division]]\n|result15=R|result16=R\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored.\n|update=complete\n|source=[http://rsssf.com/tablesr/rus01.html rsssf.com] \n}}</onlyinclude>\n\nDuring the round 22 match between Anzhi and CSKA on 18 August, CSKA and [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] goalkeeper [[Sergey Perkhun|Serhiy Perkhun]] clashed heads with Anzhi striker [[Budun Budunov]]. Both players were injured, and Perkhun died from a [[brain haemorrhage]] on 28 August in the age of 23.<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/en/news/index/0,1464,29499,00.html]</ref>\n\n== Top goalscorers ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Rank!!Name!!Goals!!Team\n|-\n|1||[[Dmitri Vyazmikin]]||18||Torpedo\n|-\n|2||[[Andrey Fedkov]]||14||Sokol\n|-\n| ||[[James Obiorah]] {{flagicon|Nigeria}}||14||Lokomotiv\n|-\n| ||[[Serghei Rogaciov]] {{flagicon|Moldova}}||14||Saturn\n|-\n|5||[[Dmitri Kirichenko]]||13||Rostselmash\n|-\n|6||[[Dmitri Loskov]]||12||Lokomotiv\n|-\n| ||[[Vitali Safronov]]||12||Fakel\n|-\n|8||[[Luis Pereira Robson|Robson]] {{flagicon|Brazil}}||11||Spartak\n|-\n| ||[[Egor Titov]]||11||Spartak\n|-\n| ||[[Valery Yesipov]]||11||Rotor\n|}\n\n==Awards==\nOn 20 November, [[Russian Football Union]] named its list of 33 top players:<ref>{{cite news |script-title=ru:\u0423\u0422\u0412\u0415\u0420\u0416\u0414\u0415\u041d \u0421\u041f\u0418\u0421\u041e\u041a 33 \u041b\u0423\u0427\u0428\u0418\u0425 |language=ru |url=http://www.sport-express.ru/art.shtml?42933 |publisher=[[Sport Express]] |date=2001-11-21 |access-date=2009-03-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041111045840/http://www.sport-express.ru/art.shtml?42933 |archive-date=2004-11-11 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<center>\n;Goalkeepers\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Ruslan Nigmatullin]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[Serhiy Perkhun]] (CSKA Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[Maxym Levitsky]] (Spartak Moscow)\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n;Right backs\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Gennadiy Nizhegorodov]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Dmitri Sennikov]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Vladimir Kurayev]] (Saturn)\n{{col-3}}\n;Centre backs\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Igor Chugainov]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Macedonia}} [[Igor Mitreski]] (Spartak Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Yevgeni Bushmanov]] (Krylia Sovetov)\n{{col-3}}\n;Left backs\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Yuri Kovtun]] (Spartak Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|South Africa}} [[Jacob Lekgetho]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Valeri Tsvetkov]] (Zenit)\n{{col-end}}\n\n;Stoppers\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Sergei Ignashevich]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Aleksei Katulsky]] (Zenit)\n#{{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[Dmytro Parfenov]] (Spartak Moscow)\n\n;Defensive midfielders\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Marat Izmailov]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Dmitri Loskov]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[Olexandr Gorshkov (footballer)|Olexandr Gorshkov]] (Zenit)\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n;Right wingers\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Rolan Gusev]] (Dynamo Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Andrei Arshavin]] (Zenit)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Andrei Konovalov]] (Krylia Sovetov)\n{{col-3}}\n;Central midfielders\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Yegor Titov]] (Spartak Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Valery Yesipov]] (Rotor)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Andrey Tikhonov]] (Krylia Sovetov)\n{{col-3}}\n;Left wingers\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Andrei Karyaka]] (Krylia Sovetov)\n#{{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[Olexandr Spivak]] (Zenit)\n#{{flagicon|Uzbekistan}} [[Ruslan Agalarov]] (Anzhi)\n{{col-end}}\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Right forwards\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Vladimir Beschastnykh]] (Spartak Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Dmitri Vyazmikin]] (Torpedo Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Nigeria}} [[James Obiorah]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n{{col-2}}\n;Left forwards\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Sergei Semak]] (CSKA Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Ruslan Pimenov]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Aleksandr Kerzhakov]] (Zenit)\n{{Col-end}}\n</center>\n\n==Medal squads==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" Width=\"700\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#FF0000\"\n| align=\"center\" width=\"700\" |<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF;\"> '''1. FC Spartak Moscow''' </span>\n|- bgcolor=\"#E8E8E8\"  \n| align=\"left\" width=\"700\" |\n'''Goalkeepers:''' [[Maksym Levytskyi]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (20), [[Aleksandr Filimonov]] (8), [[Maksim Kabanov]] (3).<br />\n'''Defenders:''' [[Igor Mitreski]] {{flagicon|MKD}} (27), [[Dmytro Parfenov]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (26 / 4), [[Yuri Kovtun]] (26  / 1), [[Jerry-Christian Tchuiss\u00e9]] {{flagicon|CMR}} (22), [[Dmitri Ananko]] (13), [[Oleksandr Hranovskyi]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (8 / 1), [[Dmitri Bugakov]] (5), [[Mikhail Kupriyanov]] (4), [[Ibra K\u00e9b\u00e9]] {{flagicon|SEN}} (4), [[Igor Stamenovski]] {{flagicon|MKD}} (1), [[Andrei Streltsov]] (1).<br />\n'''Midfielders:''' [[Yegor Titov]] (30 / 11), [[Viktor Bulatov]] (29 / 2), [[Vasili Baranov]] {{flagicon|BLR}} (25 / 5), [[Eduard Tsykhmeystruk]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (15 / 3), [[Maksym Kalynychenko]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (9 / 2), [[Aleksandr Pavlenko]] (5), [[Kahaber Mzhavanadze]] {{flagicon|GEO}} (4), [[Nikola Gjo\u0161evski]] {{flagicon|MKD}} (4), [[Lawrence Adjei]] {{flagicon|GHA}} (1), [[Yevhen Lysytsyn]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (1).<br />\n'''Forwards:''' [[Luis Robson]] {{flagicon|BRA}} (28 / 11), [[Aleksandr Shirko]] (15 / 3), [[Vladimir Beschastnykh]] (12 / 9), [[Nikolai Pisarev]] (9 / 1), [[Jafar Irismetov]] {{flagicon|UZB}} (8), [[Artyom Bezrodny]] (6 / 1), [[German Lovchev]] (5), [[Raman Vasilyuk]] {{flagicon|BLR}} (4 / 2), [[Marcos Antonio Aparecido Cipriano|Marc\u00e3o]] {{flagicon|BRA}} (3), [[Okon Flo Essien]] {{flagicon|NGA}} (3), [[Aleksandr Danishevsky]] (2), [[Aleksandr Sonin]] (2).<br />''(league appearances and goals listed in brackets)''\n\n'''Manager:''' [[Oleg Romantsev]]\n\n'''Transferred out during the season:''' [[Aleksandr Shirko]] (to [[FC Torpedo Moscow]]), [[Nikolai Pisarev]] (to [[FC Torpedo-ZIL Moscow]]), [[Oleksandr Hranovskyi]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (to {{flagicon|UKR}} [[FC Karpaty Lviv]]), [[Jafar Irismetov]] {{flagicon|UZB}} (on loan to {{flagicon|BLR}} [[FC Slavia Mozyr]]), [[Aleksandr Filimonov]] (to {{flagicon|UKR}} [[FC Dynamo Kyiv]]), [[Dmitri Bugakov]] (to [[FC Sokol Saratov]]), [[Nikola Gjo\u0161evski]] {{flagicon|MKD}} (to {{flagicon|MKD}} [[FK Vardar]]), [[Marcos Antonio Aparecido Cipriano|Marc\u00e3o]] {{flagicon|BRA}} (to {{flagicon|GER}} [[FC St. Pauli]]).\n|- bgcolor=\"#DB0500\"\n| align=\"center\" width=\"700\" |<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF;\"> '''2. FC Lokomotiv Moscow''' </span>\n|- bgcolor=\"#E8E8E8\"\n| align=\"left\" width=\"700\" |\n'''Goalkeepers:''' [[Ruslan Nigmatullin]] (27), [[Platon Zakharchuk]] (3).<br />\n'''Defenders:''' [[Igor Chugainov]] (28 / 2), [[Jacob Lekgetho]] {{flagicon|RSA}} (25), [[Yuri Drozdov (footballer)|Yuri Drozdov]] (24), [[Sergei Ignashevich]] (23), [[Gennadiy Nizhegorodov]] (21), [[Dmitri Sennikov]] (18), [[Vadim Evseev]] (13), [[Milan Obradovi\u0107]] {{flagicon|SRB}} (12 /