er|thumb|159x159px|SS Neckar in use as USS Antigone]]<br />\n|16 November 1902\nBaltimore\n|Vlach - Antonie (1887\u20131971),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2CSF-N9M|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Vlach|first=|date=1902|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Marie (1890\u20131969)\n|\n|-\n|19 March 1903\nSS Main\n\nBremen\n|6 April 1903\nBaltimore\n|Vlach - Sylvestr (1884-)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2CSN-Z7F|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Vlach|first=|date=1903|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|\n|c. 1903\n|Stipek - Frantisek (1885\u20131955)\n|\n|-\n|\n|c. 1904\n|Stipek - Jan (1883\u20131961)\n|\n|-\n|24 April 1906\n[[SS Kronprinz Wilhelm]]\nBremen[[File:The_SS_Kronprinz_Wilhelm_of_NDL_in_an_unknown_location.jpg|center|thumb]]\n|2 May 1906\nNew York\n|Stipek - Rozalie (1886-1960)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JFCC-768|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Stipek|first=|date=1906|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|30 August 1906\n[[SS Rhein (1899)|SS Rhein]]\nBremen[[File:USS_Susquehanna_(ID-3016).jpg|center|thumb|SS Rhein (converted to the USS Susquehanna)]]\n|11 September 1906\nBaltimore\n|Vlach - Josefa (1888-) [with mother Karolina Hranickova from [[Kv\u00e1\u0161\u0148ovice|Kvasnovice]] and 3 siblings],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2CSK-F9H|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Vlach|first=|date=1906|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Matej (1892\u20131982), Barbora (1894\u20131959), Josef (1899\u20131978)\n|\n|-\n|\n|c. 1907\n|Sus - Vaclav (1889\u20131970)\n|\n|-\n|24 August 1907\n[[USS President Lincoln (1907)|SS President Lin